# Cloudflare Pages SPA fallback for dynamic routes that aren't prerendered.
# Any URL matching these patterns serves the corresponding index.html with a 200
# status; Vue Router then reads the URL client-side and loads the right page.
# Same trick works for any future SPA-mode subroute we add.

/rankings/maps/*  /rankings/maps/  200
/p/*/maps         /p/:splat/       200
/p/*/recent       /p/:splat/       200
/p/*/opponents    /p/:splat/       200
/p/*/1on1         /p/:splat/       200
/p/*/4on4         /p/:splat/       200
/p/*/2on2         /p/:splat/       200
/p/*/trends       /p/:splat/       200
# First-spawn per-map pages are SPA — fall back to the prerendered landing index
# (returns 200 + boots the app); Vue Router then loads /training/first-spawn/{map}.
/training/first-spawn/*  /training/first-spawn/  200
# NOTE: do NOT add a `/p/*  /p/_fallback/  200` rule here. On Cloudflare Pages,
# `_redirects` rules take PRECEDENCE over static files, so a `/p/*` wildcard
# shadows every prerendered /p/{id}/index.html and serves the bare 2KB shell
# instead — which silently hid all profile content (incl. the AI Coach card)
# for days. Nitro auto-appends its own catch-all SPA fallback to this file at
# build time, so unmatched/new profiles already hydrate client-side without it.
